[[TITLE]] The Aster DSL
[[TAGS]] aster dsl language
[[DESCRIPTION]] An introductory document to the Aster DSL.
[[CONTENTS]]
Aster is a very tightly-knit operating system, and its applications are no
different. Each Aster application is written in the Aster DSL, with source files
tagged as "Aster Source" in the file system. Aster is a language not remarkably
unlike a mix of C and Jai in terms of semantics, but syntactically it is rather
unique.

To build Aster source code, you'll just need the built-in Aster Development
Tools that come with any installation of the operating system. Simply run the
following in your AsterOS terminal;

[[CODE:aster_shell]]
new_project; LANGUAGE:aster, TYPE:executable, "<project-name>".
[[ENDCODE]]

and you'll be set up with a complete development environment and a minimal
example for you to begin developing whatever project you have in mind. To
actually begin development, open the Aster "IDE" environment via

[[CODE:aster_shell]]
open; TYPE:project, "<project-name>".
[[ENDCODE]]

in your terminal. Provided will be completely toggleable syntax highlighting,
code completion, and a minimal LSP to detect errors, all running in the Jasmine
text editor. If you want more information specifically about the editor, please
see the [[REF;jasmine,specialized manual]]. You'll notice it's a lot like Vim.
